# TrendPulse Project 🚀

## 📌 Overview
TrendPulse is a Python-based data pipeline project that collects trending stories from the HackerNews API, processes the data, analyzes trends, and visualizes insights.

---

## 🔧 Tasks Completed

### 🟢 Task 1 — Data Collection
- Fetched top stories using HackerNews API
- Categorized stories into 5 categories:
  Technology, World News, Sports, Science, Entertainment
- Saved data as JSON file

---

### 🟡 Task 2 — Data Cleaning
- Removed duplicates and missing values
- Converted JSON data into CSV format using Pandas

---

### 🔵 Task 3 — Data Analysis
- Identified top trending category
- Calculated average scores
- Found most commented and highest scored stories

---

### 📊 Task 4 — Visualization
- Created bar charts and pie charts using Matplotlib
- Visualized category distribution and top authors

---

## 📁 Project Files

- task1_data_collection.py
- task2_data_cleaning.py
- task3_analysis.py
- task4_visualization.py

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Requests

---

## 🎯 Conclusion
This project demonstrates a complete data pipeline from data collection to visualization, helping understand trending topics and user engagement.

